olor: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">predicted that</a> &#8220;30% o=
f the days in the office will go away.&#8221;&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #=
1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Generally, =
though, people are both <strong>overestimating</strong> the likelihood that=
 companies will successfully Return to the office full-time and <strong>dra=
matically underestimating</strong> the first-, second-, and third-order imp=
acts of Remote or Hybrid work.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">To help put that into cont=
ext, we&#8217;ll explore:&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul style=3D"margin: 1em 0;"><li s=
tyle=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p styl=
e=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"><stron=
g>The Remote Hype Cycle. </strong>We all went Remote way too quickly. It&#8=
217;ll get better.</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-=
special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0;"><strong>The Risk of Return.</strong> The decision=
 isn&#8217;t up to employers, it&#8217;s up to employees. Companies that tr=
y to force a Return will lose the talent war.</p></li><li style=3D"margin: =
3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1=
a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"><strong>New Physical a=
nd Digital Solutions.</strong> Remote won&#8217;t always mean Zoom, and the=
 Office won&#8217;t always mean sitting at a desk five days a week.&nbsp;</=
p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bull=
et;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0;"><strong>Implications of Remote and Hybrid Work.</strong> The shift to=
 Remote and Hybrid is going to change everything from work itself to housin=
g, gaming, fitness, and so much more.&nbsp;</p></li></ul><p style=3D"color:=
 #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">We&#8217;=
re never going back to the way things were. Like any major dislocation, tha=
t presents massive opportunities for those who are prepared and is going to=
 completely run over those who aren&#8217;t. This essay doesn&#8217;t have =
all of the answers. Instead, it&#8217;s an exploration of the trend, new op=
tions, and some implications, and a wakeup call to get ahead of this and wi=
n the gold rush.&nbsp;</p><h3 style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-family: 'SF Com=
pact Display', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helve=
tica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI S=
ymbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.16em; margin: =
1em 0 0.625em 0;"><strong>The Remote Hype Cycle</strong></h3><p style=3D"co=
lor: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">It al=
ways feels safer to bet on the status quo. We&#8217;ve worked in offices fo=
r more than a century, and we&#8217;ll work in offices again.&nbsp;</p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em=
 0;">Partially, that&#8217;s because the burden of proof is always on the n=
