eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">It&#8217;s hard to blame him. Desktop comp=
uters and floppy disks were the norm. Laptops were clunky. And the whole ec=
osystem of wifi, lithium-ion batteries, coffee shops, cloud-based software,=
 and the millions of other things that combine to make laptops useful wasn&=
#8217;t yet in place. A laptop was a poor substitute for the real thing.&nb=
sp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 1em 0;">Those in the Return camp think that, like the laptop, remot=
e work will be for specialized niche companies, not the average one. They&#=
8217;re wrong, but it&#8217;s hard to blame them, either. Remote work today=
 isn&#8217;t very good.&nbsp;</p><ul style=3D"margin: 1em 0;"><li style=3D"=
